This PR shows that given a finite extension of fields $L/K,$ $H^1(Aut_K(L), L^\times)$ is trivial. Not sure about naming & whether this theorem should have its own file or not.

The image of a unit under any ring hom is a unit, so this should be the real action. Do we already have it but Lean doesn't find it? Otherwise we should add the most general version.
huh, I thought I tested that the action of Aut gets inferred from the action of End earlier but apparently not, guess I'll add it back
I don't think so; I get an error I'm not sure how to fix, and none of the other similar pairs of definitions in this file use `to_additive` either.
Not really; only the final instance needs to be `noncomputable` if I remove it.
In order to use the lemma, I think it is more convenient if we can specify the cocycle `f` explicitly, as it is done a few lines below. I would suggest keeping `(...)` here instead of `{...}`.
Can you use `(... := ...)` instead of `@` here? It is usually more readable.
Would it also be useful to have a def of `Representation R M A` given some commutative ring R acting compatibly on M and A? Then maybe typeclass inference can fill in the actions if R=Z?

```suggestion
both in terms of $H^1$ and in terms of cocycles being coboundaries.
```
